---
import Marketing from '../layouts/Marketing.astro'
import { OPERATOR_EMAIL } from '../config'
---

<Marketing
  title="Privacy — AppBahn"
  description="Privacy policy under GDPR Art. 13/14. AppBahn sets no cookies, runs no analytics, and self-hosts all fonts."
>
  <section class="legal">
    <div class="kicker">— Privacy</div>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="sub">
      This website is static. No cookies, no third-party scripts, no analytics. Everything we still
      touch is listed below. <a href="/datenschutz/">Deutsche Fassung</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="block">
      <h2>1. Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Controller under GDPR Art. 4(7):<br />
        <strong>Kirill Orlov</strong><br />
        Meinekestr. 21<br />
        10719 Berlin<br />
        Germany<br />
        Email: <a href={`mailto:${OPERATOR_EMAIL}`}><code>{OPERATOR_EMAIL}</code></a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <h2>2. Hosting (GitHub Pages)</h2>
      <p>
        This site is served statically via <strong>GitHub Pages</strong>, operated by GitHub, Inc.,
        88 Colin P. Kelly Jr. Street, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA. When you visit, GitHub processes
        technically necessary access data (IP address, timestamp, requested URL, referrer, user
        agent). Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in delivering and securing the
        service).
      </p>
      <p>
        The transfer to the US is based on the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (GitHub is
        DPF-certified) and EU Standard Contractual Clauses. The scope, retention, and handling of
        the logs are governed by GitHub's privacy statement (<a
          href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
          >docs.github.com</a
        >).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <h2>3. No CDN front, no third-party fonts</h2>
      <p>
        We self-host all fonts (Geist, Inter, JetBrains Mono) under <code>/fonts/</code> on the same domain.
        No data is transferred to Google, jsdelivr, Cloudflare, or any third party. This follows the LG
        München I ruling of 20.01.2022 (Az. 3 O 17493/20). GitHub Pages serves the site directly; no additional
        CDN is interposed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <h2>4. Email contact</h2>
      <p>
        When you email us (<code>{OPERATOR_EMAIL}</code>), we retain your message and sender address
        to handle the inquiry. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in answering
        you). Email correspondence is deleted at most two years after the matter is closed, subject
        to statutory retention obligations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <h2>5. No analytics, no trackers, no cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This site sets no cookies, loads no external scripts (no Google Analytics, Plausible,
        Fathom, no Cloudflare fronting, no GitHub embeds), and measures no traffic. A consent banner
        under TTDSG §25 is therefore not required.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <h2>6. RSS subscription</h2>
      <p>
        Our blog and changelog feeds are static XML files. We cannot tell who subscribes; no
        personal data is collected.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You have the right, at any time, to access (Art. 15), rectification (Art. 16), erasure (Art.
        17), restriction of processing (Art. 18), data portability (Art. 20), and objection (Art.
        21) regarding your personal data held by us. Please contact <code>{OPERATOR_EMAIL}</code>.
      </p>
      <p>
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. The competent
        authority is the <strong
          >Berliner Beauftragte für Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit</strong
        >
        (<a href="https://www.datenschutz-berlin.de/">datenschutz-berlin.de</a>).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="block">
      <h2>8. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We update this notice when technical or legal circumstances require it. The current version
        is always available at <code>/privacy</code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="footnote">Last updated: {new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10)}.</p>
  </section>
</Marketing>

<style>
  section.legal {
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .block {
    margin-top: 40px;
  }
  .block h2 {
    font-size: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .block p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.65;
    font-size: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .block p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .block p strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .block p a,
  .sub a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .block p a:hover,
  .sub a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.92em;
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  p.footnote {
    margin-top: 56px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
</style>
